<subSubSection id="C30393CC141DFFBA6697FBC2F374FB4F" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA6C047141DFFBA6697FBC2F601FB33" blockId="8.[151,1436,885,1269]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA6697FBC2F338FBA7" bold="true" box="[199,317,1029,1053]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to Rosalie de Lamarck, her father’s collection contained 
<specimenCount id="9D1F0BCE141DFFBA621BFBC2F706FBA7" box="[1099,1283,1029,1053]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
. However, as none of the specimens currently in the Lamarck collection matches Lamarck or Kiener’s figures, nor Lamarck’s stated sizes, it is unlikely that these are Lamarck’s original specimens. Confusingly, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF88BDB6141DFFBA620EFB8AF710FBDF" author="Lamarck &amp; J. B. P. A" box="[1118,1301,1101,1125]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11267" refString="Lamarck, [J. B. P. A.] (1822) Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertebres ... Paris. 7 (2), 711 pp." type="book" year="1822">Lamarck (1822)</bibRefCitation>
lists 
<taxonomicName id="4C19BBC4141DFFBA6304FB89F36CFB33" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lignarius">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA6304FB89F2F9FB33" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Murex lignarius</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of this species. This is a different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA6C047141DFFBA6697FB52F374FB4F" blockId="8.[151,1436,885,1269]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA6697FB52F02BFB14" bold="true" box="[199,558,1173,1198]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Current taxonomic position:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C19BBC4141DFFBA646FFB52F1CAFB17" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[575,975,1173,1197]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cornea">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA646FFB52F0F6FB17" box="[575,755,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthria cornea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF88BDB6141DFFBA655BFB52F1C2FB17" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[779,967,1173,1197]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11299" refString="Linnaeus, C. von. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae. Editio decima, reformata. Vol. 1. Regnum animale. Stockholm. 824, iii pp." type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus id="54A27EE5141DFFBA65B5FB51F610FB14" box="[997,1045,1174,1198]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C19BBC4141DFFBA62E0FB52F799FB17" authority="Gray, 1850" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1850" box="[1200,1436,1173,1197]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA62E0FB52F703FB17" box="[1200,1286,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF88BDB6141DFFBA6346FB52F799FB17" author="Gray, J. E." box="[1302,1436,1173,1197]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref10511" refString="Gray, J. E. (1850) [New generic assignments] In: M. E. Gray. Figures of molluscous animals, selected from various authors. Etched for the use of students. Volume 4. Explanations of plates and list of genera. London: Longman, Brown, Green and Longmans. iv, 219 pp." type="book" year="1850">Gray, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="4C19BBC4141DFFBA66CDFB7EF326FB6B" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[157,291,1209,1233]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Buccinidae</taxonomicName>
], placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C19BBC4141DFFBA643EFB7EF1E9FB6B" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[622,1004,1209,1233]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cornea">
<emphasis id="B96D1C55141DFFBA643EFB7EF118FB6B" box="[622,797,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthria cornea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF88BDB6141DFFBA6560FB7EF1E1FB6B" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[816,996,1209,1233]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11299" refString="Linnaeus, C. von. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae. Editio decima, reformata. Vol. 1. Regnum animale. Stockholm. 824, iii pp." type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF88BDB6141DFFBA6270FB7EF6D1FB6B" author="Bellardi, L." box="[1056,1236,1209,1233]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="33 - 294" refId="ref9324" refString="Bellardi, L. (1873) I molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonte e della Liguria. Parte 1. Cephalopoda, Pteropoda, Heteropoda, Gastropoda (Muricidae et Tritonidae). Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Serie Seconda, 27: 33 - 294, pls. 1 - 15. [Also issued as a separate, 264 pp.]." type="book chapter" year="1873">Bellardi (1873)</bibRefCitation>
